title: Rice export prices worldwide 2011 - 2018 , by variety
summary: The given chart is of multi-line type with 5 lines namely U.S. Long Grain 2.4, U.S. California Medium Grain 1.4, Thai Parboiled 100, India 25, and Pak Basmati. The y axis represents Price in USD per ton and the x axis represents Year.
Overall Thai Parboiled 100 is gradually decreasing, U.S. Long Grain 2.4, U.S. California Medium Grain 1.4, India 25, and Pak Basmati are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
Throughout the period, Pak Basmati generally had the highest Price in USD per ton relative to others with an average of 1086.38, and it reached its maximum at 2013 with a value of 1372.0.
Followed by U.S. California Medium Grain 1.4 which ranks as the second topmpost line , with an average of 788.4 Price in USD per ton,reaching its highest point  at 2014 with a value of 1007.0.
India 25 mostly had the least Price in USD per ton with a mean value of 373.0, which peaked at 2011 with a value of 409.0.
India 25 reported the lowest Price in USD per ton about 333.0 in Year 2016
